  "body": "## Requirement - what kind of business use case are you trying to solve?\r\n\r\nUnder Windows (and Powershell), setting just ``BADGER_EPHEMERAL = false`` and ``SPAN_STORAGE_TYPE = badger`` is not enough. The default directories (start dir + data + key/value) use hardcoded delimiter.\r\n\r\n## Problem - what in Jaeger blocks you from solving the requirement?\r\n\r\nStarting under Windows without setting badger's key and value directory manually.\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\"level\":\"fatal\",\"ts\":1562251290.8270292,\"caller\":\"all-in-one/main.go:104\",\"msg\":\"Failed to init storage factory\",\"error\":\"Error Creating Dir: \\\"C:\\\\\\\\projects\\\\\\\\jaeger/data/keys\\\": mkdir C:\\\\projects\\\\jaeger/data/keys: The system cannot find the path specified.\",\"errorVerbose\":\"mkdir C:\\\\projects\\\\jaeger/data/keys: The system cannot find the path specified.\\nError Creating Dir: \\\"C:\\\\\\\\projects\\\\\\\\jaeger/data/keys\\\"\\ngithub.com/jaegertracing/jaeger/vendor/github.com/dgraph-io/badger/y.Wrapf\\n\\\r\n```\r\n",
